# CloudFormation Rules

## Naming Convention

- Stack names: `vibe-dating-{service}-{stack}-{environment}` (e.g., `vibe-dating-user-lambda-dev`)
- Resource names: `vibe-dating-{resource}-{environment}` (e.g., `vibe-dating-media-dev`)
- All resources must have `Environment` and `Service` tags

## Stack Organization

Each service has numbered stacks deployed in order:
```
src/services/{service}/cloudformation/
  01-iam.yaml
  02-lambda.yaml
  03-apigateway.yaml
```

## Parameters

- Use `src/config/parameters.yaml` for environment-specific values
- Common parameters: `Environment`, `DeploymentUUID`, `ApiRegion`, `ApiDomainName`
- Reference cross-stack outputs via CloudFormation exports

## Lambda Configuration

- Runtime: `python3.11`
- Memory: 128-256 MB (adjust per function needs)
- Timeout: 30s default, longer for media processing
- Environment variables from Secrets Manager ARNs (not plaintext secrets)

## Security

- IAM roles follow least-privilege principle
- DynamoDB uses KMS encryption
- S3 blocks public access
- API Gateway uses custom JWT authorizer
